In article <OZ.93Aug6155030@ursa.sis.yorku.ca> oz@ursa.sis.yorku.ca (Ozan S. Yigit) writes:
> because, quite literally, i just swung over to the console of the system
> that hosts it, and initialized it myself.

Fine. I'm talking about the limitations of cryptography, not of physics.

> i understand your point, but i
> am not sure if it is a practical one, or a gedankenexperiment.

It's a practical one: you shouldn't bother implementing a complex
cryptographic protocol whose claimed benefit is that ``it stops 
man-in-the-middle attacks.'' Such claims are _always_ incorrect.

